<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06039j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06039j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06039j"> 39(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fruit of colonies (lemon)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Une petite amie de Loti (elle avait six ans et lui sept), &agrave; propos d&apos;un abricot qu&apos;ils venaient d&apos;ouvrir pour le partager, lui racontait dans un coin du jardin cette histoire: &ldquo;Une fois, une petite fille... en ouvrant <mark>un fruit des colonies</mark> tr&egrave;s gros... il en &eacute;tait sorti une b&ecirc;te, un b&ecirc;te verte... qui l&apos;avait piqu&eacute;e... et puis &ccedil;a l&apos;avait fait mourir.&rdquo; &mdash; &ldquo;Dans cette histoire, dit Loti, ce passage &agrave; lui seul m&apos;avait subitement jet&eacute; dans une r&ecirc;verie:&rdquo; ... un fruit des colonies tr&egrave;s gros.&rdquo; <font color="green">[A girlfriend of Loti (she was six and he seven), about an apricot they had just opened to share, told him in a corner of the garden this story: &ldquo;Once, a little girl. .. by opening a fruit of the colonies very big ... it had left a beast, a green beast ... who had stung ... and then it had killed him.&rdquo; In this story, said Loti, this passage alone had suddenly thrown me into a reverie]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
